  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 5:41",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ταλιθά",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "κοῦμ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", maiden, rise! first instance in which the words of Jesus, as spoken in Aramaic, are given. Jesus may have been a bilingual, sometimes using Greek, sometimes Syriac. He would use the vernacular on a pathetic occasion like this. The word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ταλιθά",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", feminine of Teli (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "טְלִי",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), is found in the Hebrew only in the plural (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "טְלָאִים",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "41",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Talitha cumi",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] = “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Little Maid, arise.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "” Doubtless St Peter, who was now present, often recalled the actual words used on this memorable occasion by our Lord, and told them to his friend and kinsman St Mark. So it is the same Evangelist, who preserves the very word, which our Lord used, when He opened the ears of the deaf man, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ephphatha",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 7:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The mention of these words goes to prove that in ordinary life our Lord availed Himself of the popular Aramaic dialect.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 5:41",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ταλιθὰ κοῦμι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Talitha Cumi",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Peter had remembered the precise words used by the Saviour; and it was from his mouth [dictation] that Mark is said to have written. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Talitha",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " was used but once; for Jesus, in raising the dead, did not employ Epizeuxis [repetition of the same word; see Append.], ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 7:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 11:43",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". For His power was always instantaneous in its effect; comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 20:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "σοὶ λέγω",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I say unto thee",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") This is not contained in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Talitha Cumi",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and yet it is with truth added.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
